{
  "text": "Intravesical delivery of photosensitizer avoids, in part, the build up of photosensitizer in adjacent tissues. In the case of urinary bladder tumors, this method of delivery has been shown to cause selective urothelial ablation without lamina propria or detrusor muscle damage. This technique represents a significant refinement in the precise application of laser energy to selectively destroy malignant tumor cells. [CITATION_1] ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "29791498"
